Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
route_pg(25.10)                                                route_pg(25.10)

Name
       route_pg

Syntax
       route_pg

       [-help]

       [-check_psdl_only]

       [-delete_floating]

       [-fast]

       [-psdl_file <file_name>]

       [-skip_block_pin]

       [-skip_partial_overlap_via]

       [-skip_physical_pin]

       [-skip_via]

       [-stop_on_error]

       [-use_full_pattern]

       [-use_namespace]

       [-write_psdl <output_file>]

       Uses  the  Innovus  database,  builds the region with the help of PSDL,
       where the PG structure is to be created, and parses  it.  This  command
       also uses all the syntax in PSDL to build the PG structure.

       The  following  figure  presents the process of developing a PG routing
       flow using the route_pg command:

       Parameters

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each route_pg parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man route_pg

       -check_psdl_only
              Performs sanity check only on the PSDL input file.

       -delete_floating
              Removes floating wires.

       -fast  Generates PG routing flow in the Fast PG mode.

       -psdl_file <file_name>
              Specifies the PSDL input file.

       -skip_block_pin
              Skips the formation of connection to the block pins.

       -skip_partial_overlap_via
              Skips building of via on partial overlap intersection.  See  the
              example below:

       -skip_physical_pin
              Skips  generation  of  physical pins, when the stripes touch the
              design boundary.

       -skip_via
              Skips building via object.

       -stop_on_error
              Stops the PG route process if there is any critical or non-crit-
              ical/recoverable error in the PSDL file. When this parameter  is
              not  specified,  the  Flash PG engine stops the PG route process
              only if there is any critical error in the PSDL file.

              Critical errors in the PSDL file include:

              * Syntax errors

              * NRPG-75 warning

              * When the specified variable name does not exist

              * When the specified Tcl variable does not exist  or  its  value
                does not meet the required format

              Non-critical/recoverable errors in the PSDL file include:

              * Missing  values that can easily be extracted/obtained from the
                design data or tech LEF

              * Duplicate definitions/syntaxes

       -use_full_pattern
              Allows route_pg to accept only a whole pattern set for  building
              the PG structure region when Flash PG reaches the end of the re-
              gion, or when there are DRC violations in its surrounding.. When
              this  parameter is not specified,  route_pg can also accept par-
              tial region set.

       -use_namespace
              Uses namespace for metal Id.

       -write_psdl <output_file>
              Writes a PSDL file to ensure that the input numerical/string Tcl
              variable is correctly calculated and applied.

Examples
              * The following command checks the -psdl_file syntax only (with-
                out running the route_pg command):

                route_pg -fast -psdl_file <filename> -check_psdl_only

              * The following command removes a floating wire:

                route_pg -fast -psdl_file <psdl_file> -delete_floating

              * The following command does not generate via while running  the
                route_pg command:

                route_pg -fast -psdl_file <psdl_file> -skip_via

              * The following command skips partial generated vias:

                route_pg   -fast  -psdl_file  <psdl_file>  -skip_partial_over-
                lap_via

              * The following command generates a PG structure in the Fast  PG
                mode and writes a PSDL file during its run:

                route_pg   -fast   -psdl_file  <file_name>  -write_psdl  <out-
                put_file>

              * The following command generates a PG structure in the Complete
                PG mode and writes a PSDL file during its run:

                route_pg -psdl_file <file_name> -write_psdl <output_file>

              * The following command checks the PSDL syntax and writes a PSDL
                file without generating the PG structure:

                route_pg -psdl_file <file_name>  -check_psdl_only  -write_psdl
                <output_file>

